cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it addresses semantic segmentation tasks in images and videos. It also incorporates a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) to solve Markov Random Field (MRF) for semantic segmentation, which is a common approach in computer vision. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a deep learning model for semantic segmentation. Other possible sub-categories include Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as the paper addresses a task related to intelligent systems, Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as semantic segmentation can also be applied to natural language processing tasks, and Multimedia (cs.MM) as the proposed model can be applied to both images and videos.
